- NoSQL database
Types of Database Management System
1. RDBMS
2. NoSQL
3. OLAP(Online Analytical Processing)

NoSQL
- scalable & faster

when to use NoSql
- want to store & retrieve huge amount of data
- relationship between the data are not important
- data is not structured
- data is growing continuously

MongoDB
- open source
- document oriented database that means data is stored in the form of documents(Key-Value pair) JSON format called BSON
	database----> database
	table-------> Collections
	rows--------> Document
	columns------> fields

Commands
1. use springpractice
2. show dbs;
3. db.user.insert({name:"aditya",age:25}); //  db.createCollection("student")
4. db.user.find().pretty();
5. db.dropDatabase();
6.
db.createUser(
  {
    user: "admin",
    pwd:  passwordPrompt(),
    roles: [ { role: "readWrite", db: "springpractice" },
             { role: "read", db: "test" } ]
  }
)

7.  mongosh --port 27017 -u "admin" --authenticationDatabase "springpractice" -p
8. db.customer.createIndex({city:"text",customerName:"text"});
9. db.customer.find({address:{$regex: 'Near Sadashiv PETH',$options:"i"}});